All the revelations that ever saw any man here in bodily likeness in
this life, they have ghostly meanings. And I trow that if they unto
whom they were showed had been so ghostly, or could have conceived
their meanings ghostly, that then they had never been showed bodily.
And therefore let us pick off the rough bark, and feed us with the
sweet kernel.
